    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - DISASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">This view (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302363">Figure 63</hotlnk>) of the countershaft shows the direction of the gears. The
                gears are secured with three keys.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302363" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302363" filename="../figg13/G1302363.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Countershaft Disassembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If a straight edge is placed between the teeth (painted here to show the timing marks),
                every gear on the countershaft will be in line with the blind spline on the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302364">Figure 64</hotlnk>). When the shafts are in time, these marks will be directly
                across from each other.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302364" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302364" filename="../figg13/G1302364.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Straight Edge Between Teeth</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
